h let us calculate quantities that describe groups of data. \nLearn the basics of joining tables together in R with dplyr. Learn to use R or manually calculate the mean, median, and mode of real-world datasets. In this module, you will learn how to quantify the spread of the dataset by calculating the variance and standard deviation in R. In this course, you will learn how to calculate three important descriptive statistics that describe the spread of the data. Learn about the statistics used to run hypothesis tests. Then, learn how to use R to run different t-tests that compare distributions.','Codecademy','ggplot2, tidyr, R, dplyr',4.6,9794,4500000,'20:00:00',72000,0,0,'Beginner','Data Science','English'),('COURSE_004','Learn Data Visualization with Python','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/data-visualization-python','Master a commonly used Python graphing module, Matplotlib. Soon, you will be producing high-quality plots to visualize your data. Use Seaborn, a Python data visualization library, to create bar charts for statistical analysis.','Codecademy','Matplotlib, Python, Seaborn',4.6,9794,4500000,'06:00:00',21600,0,0,'Intermediate','Data Science','English'),('COURSE_005','Data Scientist','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/paths/data-science','Start off with an overview of what you\'ll cover in the Data Scientist career path, projects you\'ll build, and resources you\'ll benefit from. Start with a quick introduction to Data Science: what it is, how it works, and how it\'s shaping the future of the technology industry. Learn the fundamentals of Python from syntax to modules. Use your understanding of Python syntax to sort and analyze data about U.S. medical insurance costs! Learn about various methods of acquiring data. Gain an overview of data manipulation and data analysis with pandas, and introduce Python lambda functions. Most data scientists spend the bulk of their time preprocessing data. Learn how to do it right. Learn about methods for summarizing and inspecting quantitative data. Learn how to design and conduct a hypothesis test in Python. Use data visualization to better explore and analyze your data. Use your understanding of data visualization to analyze and plot data about GDP and life expectancy. Communication is an important part of your work as a data scientist. Learn best practices for effectively explaining your analysis. Use your knowledge of data analysis to interpret data about endangered animals for the National Park Service. Learn the basics of Natural Language Processing - a field focused on programming computers to understand natural languages like English! Learn the basics of Machine Learning while investigating several supervised learning techniques. Dip your toes into unsupervised machine learning with K-Means clustering, hierarchical clustering, and PCA. Get ready to dive headfirst into deep learning fundamentals! Use your knowledge of machine learning to build, train, and test predictions you draw about data from OKCupid. Build on your SQL knowledge to prepare yourself for data scientist interviews. Show off your knowledge of data science by developing your final portfolio project on a topic of your choice.','Codecademy','Machine Learning, Microsoft SQL Server, PCA, Python, NLP, Pandas, SQL, NumPy, Matplotlib, Scikit-learn, Python 3, Deep Learning',4.6,9794,1625989,'22:00:00',252000,0,0,'Intermediate','Data Science','English'),('COURSE_006','Analyze data with Python','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/paths/analyze-data-with-python','Prepare to learn Data Analysis by understanding how and why it is used. Learn the fundamentals of Python, one of the most popular programming languages for Data Analysis. Learn about NumPy, a Python library used to store arrays of numbers, organize large amounts of data, and perform statistical calculations. Learn the basics of Pandas, an industry standard Python library that provides tools for data manipulation and analysis. Data Visualization with Matplotlib. Learn how to calculate and interpret several descriptive statistics using the Python library NumPy. Learn SciPy, a Python module for comparative statistics, in order to perform many different statistical tests in code. Put your new analysis skills to work with a series of case studies and capstone projects.','Codecademy','Matplotlib, NumPy, SciPy, Python, Pandas, Jupyter',4.6,9794,1625989,'20:00:00',72000,0,0,'Intermediate','Data Science','English'),('COURSE_007','Analyze data with SQL','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/paths/analyze-data-with-sql','Learn the basics of SQL databases and build your own. Write your own queries to access data and apply your SQL knowledge to complete real-world projects. Increase the number of tools in your SQL toolset by learning about aggregates, then apply them to datasets to discover new insights. Expand your abilities by joining multiple sources of data. Going Off-Platform. Set up a SQL database on your own computer and practice the commands you\'ve learned. Analyze Real Data with SQL. Combine everything that you learned to solve real business problems. Dive into the more advanced SQL topics like window functions, math functions, and date functions.','Codecademy','SQL, Command Line, SQLite',4.6,9794,1625989,'12:00:00',43200,0,0,'Intermediate','Data Science','English'),('COURSE_008','Analyze financial data with Python','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/paths/finance-python','Learn the basics of Python, one of the world\'s most popular and powerful programming languages, and see how it can be utilized in finance. Learn the basics of NumPy, a Python package for handling large, multi-dimensional arrays and matrices, to quicken your financial analyses. Learn the basics of Pandas, a Python package for data manipulation and analysis, and discover how to access financial data from APIs. Learn the basics of Matplotlib, a Python package for data visualization, and discover how to optimize a portfolio of stocks. Learn the basics of Regression, a statistical modeling technique for estimating the relationships between variables.','Codecademy','Matplotlib, NumPy, Python, API, Pandas, APIs',4.6,9794,1625989,'14:00:00',50400,0,0,'Intermediate','Data Science','English'),('COURSE_009','Design Databases With PostgreSQL','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/paths/design-databases-with-postgresql','Learn how to write basic queries to get information out of the databases you\'re working with. Learn how to properly design a database by learning about database schemas, relationships, and keys. Learn how to add constraints to your database. Learn how to optimize your database by using indexes and normalization.','Codecademy','PostgreSQL, SQL',4.6,9794,1625989,'06:00:00',108000,0,0,'Intermediate','Data Science','English'),('COURSE_010','Learn Statistics with Python','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/learn-statistics-with-python','Learn to use Python packages or manually calculate the mean, median, and mode of real-world datasets. Learn how to quantify the spread of the dataset by calculating the variance and standard deviation. Learn how to visualize and interpret a dataset using a histogram. Learn how to describe a statistical distribution by considering its center, shape, spread, and outliers. Learn how to calculate three important descriptive statistics that describe the spread of the data. Learn how to create and interpret boxplots using a variety of different datasets','Codecademy','Python',4.6,9794,4500000,'15:00:00',54000,0,0,'Intermediate','Data Science','English'),('COURSE_011','Learn Python 3','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/learn-python-3','Python syntax in this lesson and then create a point of sale system for a furniture store. Learn about code reuse with Python functions. Apply that knowledge to create functions for famous physics formulas. Learn how to build control flow into your python code by including if, else, and elif statements as well as try and except statements. Expect to learn all you need to know about boolean variables and logical operators. Learn about lists, a data structure in Python used to store ordered groups of data. Loops are structures that let you repeat Python code over and over. Learn how to read loops and write them to solve your own problems. Learn all about the Python string object. Figure out how to automatically create, rearrange, reassign, disassemble, and reassemble blocks of text. Learn how modules work in the Python programming language. Learn all about the Python dictionary structure and how to create and use key-value pairs in your code. Learn how to work with files in an automated way! Investigate the properties of text, CSV, and JSON files by reading and writing to them. Learn about the differences between data types in Python and how to create your own classes, objects, and interfaces. Use the full potential of Python functions. Learn about different ways to declare, call, and interact with functions.','Codecademy','CSV, Json, Python 3, Text Mining',4.6,9794,4500000,'06:00:00',21600,0,0,'Intermediate','Data Science','English'),('COURSE_012','Build Deep Learning Models with TensorFlow','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/paths/build-deep-learning-models-with-tensorflow','Overview of material in the build Deep Learning Models with Tensorflow skill path. Foundations of Deep Learning and Perceptrons. Before developing your own models, take a dive into deep learning fundamentals. Getting Started with TensorFlow. Build your own neural networks using TensorFlow. Classification. Take a dive into classification models, including image classification, with deep learning neural networks. Deep Learning in the Real World. Deeper dives into applications of deep learning and how you can use your skills to solve real-world problems. Deep Learning Portfolio Project. Put your deep learning skills to the test with your very own portfolio project.','Codecademy','Tensorflow, Deep Learning, Python, Keras, NumPy, Machine Learning',4.6,9794,1625989,'06:00:00',21600,0,0,'Intermediate','Data Science','English'),('COURSE_013','Master Statistics with Python','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/paths/master-statistics-with-python','Learn about variable types and how to store them in Python. Learn how to summarize quantitative data in Python using summary statistics. Learn how to visualize and describe a distribution of quantitative data using histograms, box plots, and quantiles/quartiles. Summary Statistics for Categorical Data. Learn how to summarize categorical variables in Python using numerical summary statistics. Learn how to investigate whether there is an association between two variables. Learn about hypothesis testing and how to design an experiment in Python.','Codecademy','Python, Pandas, NumPy, SciPy, Matplotlib',4.6,9794,1625989,'08:00:00',28800,0,0,'Intermediate','Data Science','English'),('COURSE_014','Learn Statistics with R','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/learn-statistics-with-r','Learn R: Mean, Median, Mode. Learn to use R or manually calculate the mean, median, and mode of real-world datasets.Learn R: Variance and Standard Deviation. In this module, you will learn how to quantify the spread of the dataset by calculating the variance and standard deviation in R.Learn R: Quartiles, Quantiles and Interquartile range. In this course, you will learn how to calculate three important descriptive statistics that describe the spread of the data.Learn R: Hypothesis testing. Learn about the statistics used to run hypothesis tests. Then, learn how to use R to run different t-tests that compare distributions.','Codecademy','R',4.6,9794,4500000,'10:00:00',36000,0,0,'Intermediate','Data Science','English'),('COURSE_015','Learn Conversational Design with Alexa','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/alexa-conversational-design','Entity Resolution (SDK v1). Learn how to handle synonyms with entity resolution. Dialog Management (SDK v1). Create engaging conversations with Dialog Management','Codecademy','Dialog Management (SDK v1), Amazon Alexa, AWS Lambda, GitHub',4.6,9794,4500000,'07:00:00',25200,0,0,'Intermediate','Data Science','English'),('COURSE_016','Learn Node-SQLite','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/learn-node-sqlite','Learn Node- SQLite. Learn how to interact with a SQL database from within your JavaScript programs in this course on the \'node-sqlite3\' package.','Codecademy','SQL, JavaScript, SQLite',4.6,9794,12505,'01:00:00',3600,0,0,'Intermediate','Data Science','English'),('COURSE_017','Learn How to Get Started with Natural Language Processing','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/natural-language-processing','Getting Started with Natural Language Processing. Delve into the exciting world of Natural Language Processing (NLP) with this overview of major topics in the field. Introduction to regular expressions. Get a taste of regular expressions (regex), a powerful search pattern language to quickly find the text you\'re looking for. Text Prepocessing. Before most natural language processing tasks, it\'s necessary to clean up the text data using text preprocessing techniques.Language Parsing. Apply regular expressions (regex) and other natural language parsing tactics to find meaning and insights in the texts you read every day.\nBag - of - words language model. Whet your language model appetite with the widely used Bag-of-Words. Develop the underlying functionality in Python, then use scikit-learn.Term frequency - inverse document frequency. Rethink topic models with term frequency-inverse document frequency (tf-idf), which adjusts the importance of words within a document. Word Embedding. Reframe word meaning based on context using word embeddings, a natural language processing technique to map words in relation to each other. Deep learning and text generation. Learn about seq2seq and LSTM neural networks commonly used in NLP work and how to implement them for machine translation.','Codecademy','NLP, Python',4.6,9794,4500000,'01:00:00',3600,0,0,'Intermediate','Data Science','English'),('COURSE_018','Learn Data Analysis with Pandas','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/data-processing-pandas','Introduce to Pandas. Use Pandas to create and manipulate tables so that you can process your data faster and get your insights sooner. Aggregates in Pandas. Learn the basics of aggregate functions in Pandas, which let us calculate quantities that describe groups of data. Multiple Tables in Pandás. Learn how to combine information from multiple DataFrames.','Codecademy','Pandas, Python, SciPy, Matplotlib',4.6,9794,4500000,'06:00:00',21600,0,0,'Intermediate','Data Science','English'),('COURSE_019','Learn Statistics with NumPy','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/intro-statistics-numpy','Introduction to NumPy. Get acquainted with NumPy, a Python library used to store arrays of numbers, and learn basic syntax and functionality. Statistics in NumPy. Learn how to analyze different statistical distributions using NumPy.','Codecademy','NumPy, Python',4.6,9794,4500000,'05:00:00',18000,0,0,'Intermediate','Data Science','English'),('COURSE_020','Computer Science','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/paths/computer-science','Introduction to Programming. Kickstart your coding life as you learn all about the programming language Python and the techniques used when writing it. Development Skills. Learn about the tools for software development. Learn to navigate the terminal and keep snapshots of your work using git. Flow, Data, and iteration. Learn all about control flow, storage of data in Python, and how to loop over things. Build a Tourism Recommendation Engine. Develop your own application using the Python programming language, the terminal, and git! Use your coding skills to make a tourism recommendation service. Python Objects. Learn about creating and using objects in Python with these courses on some of the most commonly used data types. Then unlock your full potential by learning how to create your own with classes. Create an Art Marketplace. Learn about building and creating data types and objects in this course that focuses on creating a specialized marketplace for art traders. Linear Data Structures. Learn about virtualization of computer memory by building the fundamental data structures of computer science: lists, stacks, and queues. Learn Complex Data Structures. Discover and design new data structures that follow abstract rule-based systems by building out graphs, hash-maps, and heaps. Data Structures Review. After learning about data structures, take some time to review and compare them. Asymptotic Notation. Learn how to analyze performance of algorithms in a general way using asymptotic notation. Learn Recursion with Python. Recursion gives you a new perspective on problem-solving by defining a problem in terms of itself. Learn Sorting Algorithms with Python. Learn about the usefulness and efficiency of computational sorting by implementing different sorting algorithms yourself. How to Implement Search Algorithms with Python. Finding the data you are looking for in a data set is an important skill: get started with two common approaches. Graph Search Algorithms. Learn how to explore and graph the information you are looking for.','Codecademy','Python, Data Structures, Graph Database, Command Line, Git, PostgreSQL',4.6,9794,1625989,'16:00:00',144000,0,0,'Beginner','Computer Science','English'),('COURSE_021','Learn Hardware Programming with CircuitPython','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/learn-circuitpython','Set up the Circuit Playground Express and light up some colors using the NeoPixels. Learn about the advanced features of Circuit Playground Express including its sensors, audio output, and capacitive touches','Codecademy','Python, CircuitPython',4.6,9794,4500000,'05:00:00',18000,0,0,'Beginner','Computer Science','English'),('COURSE_022','Learn C#','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/learn-c-sharp','Learn about C#, a programming language used for websites, apps, video games, and virtual reality. Learn about how types and variables are used in C#. Learn how to work with Boolean logic and conditional statements in C#. Learn to call and create methods: a fundamental building block in C# development. Learn how to organize data and automate repetitive tasks with arrays and loops. Define your own custom types using classes. Organize, secure, and simplify your code with interfaces and inheritance. Unlock the power of references: an essential aspect of object-oriented programming in C#. Work with data in C# using lists and LINQ queries','Codecademy','LinQ, C#, OOP',4.6,9794,4500000,'06:00:00',108000,0,0,'Beginner','Computer Science','English'),('COURSE_023','Learn the Basics of Blockchain with Python','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/introduction-to-blockchain','Fundamental Blockchain Concepts. Learn the fundamental concepts that allow all blockchains to function. Blockchain in Python. Build your own mini blockchain in Python','Codecademy','Blockchain, Python',4.6,9794,4500000,'02:00:00',7200,0,0,'Beginner','Computer Science','English'),('COURSE_024','Pass the Technical Interview with JavaScript','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/paths/pass-the-technical-interview-with-javascript','Getting Started with Data Structures. Get started with an overview of data structures, algorithms, and dig into building your first data structure. JavaScript Linear Data Structures. Learn to build various linear abstract data types in JavaScript, such as linked lists, queues, and stacks. Hash Maps. Learn hash maps, a key-value data storage structure with very efficient lookup performance. Algorithmic Concepts. Learn algorithm fundamentals, including recursive vs. iterative patterns and Big O asymptotic notation. Nonlinear Data Structures. Learn to build various nonlinear data structures such as Trees, Binary Trees, and Heaps. Sorting Algorithms. Learn how to build essential sorting algorithms, such as bubble sort, merge sort, and quicksort. Graph Data Structures. Learn how to create, traverse, and find paths through graph data structures. JavaScript interview prep and Algorithm Practice. Learn key interview preparation skills and practice algorithmic problem-solving in JavaScript.','Codecademy','Graph Database, JavaScript, Big O, Sort Algorithm, Search Algorithm, Nonlinear Data Structures, Linear Data Structures',4.6,9794,1625989,'16:00:00',57600,0,0,'Intermediate','Computer Science','English'),('COURSE_025','Pass the Technical Interview with Python','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/paths/pass-the-technical-interview-with-python','Welcome to interview prep in Python. Get started with an overview of data structures, algorithms, and dig into building your first data structure. Linear Data Structures. Learn to build various linear abstract data types in Python, such as linked lists, queues, and stacks. Hash Maps. Learn about hash maps, a key-value data storage structure with very efficient lookup performance. Algorithmic Concepts. Learn algorithm fundamentals, including recursive vs. iterative patterns and Big O asymptotic notation. Nonlinear Data Structures. A conceptual and Python-specific introduction to Trees, Binary Search Trees, and Heaps. Sorting Algorithms. Learn about sorting algorithms in Python. Graphs and Graph Traversals. Learn to build a Graph in Python, and then traverse it using depth-first search, breadth-first search, and Dijkstra\'s and A* algorithms. interview prep and practice problems. Learn some common interviewing tricks and tips. Then practice some real interview questions in Python.','Codecademy','Graph Database, Binary Search, Linear Data Structures, Python, Big O, Sort Algorithm, Search Algorithm, Nonlinear Data Structures, DFS, BFS',4.6,9794,1625989,'16:00:00',57600,0,0,'Intermediate','Computer Science','English'),('COURSE_026','Learn Complex Data Structures','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/complex-data-structures','Learn about hash maps, the efficient key-value storage used in many different programming languages, and then implement one yourself. Learn Trees. Learn the tree data structure using Python and create an adventure game. Learn Heaps. Learn the data structure of heaps using Python. A heap is a specialized type of tree with many applications.\nLearn Graphs. Learn the graphs data structure using Python. Graphs are the perfect data structure for modeling networks!','Codecademy','Python, Graph Database, Linear Data Structures',4.6,9794,4500000,'10:00:00',36000,0,0,'Intermediate','Computer Science','English'),('COURSE_027','Technical Interview Practice with Python','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/technical-interview-practice-python','Technical Interviews: WhiteBoadrding. Practice your whiteboarding skills and learn how to break a technical interview problem down into manageable pieces. Technical Interviews Problems: Lists. A collection of common interview problems that use the Python List, and strategies for how to construct optimal solutions. Technical Interviews Problems: Linked Lists. A collection of common interview problems that use the linked list data structure, and strategies for how to construct optimal solutions. Technical Interviews Problems: Dynamic Programming. Dynamic Programming is a technique we can apply to difficult questions that ask us to maximize a value given many options or constraints.','Codecademy','Python, Data Structures',4.6,9794,4500000,'05:00:00',18000,0,0,'Intermediate','Computer Science','English'),('COURSE_028','How to Implement Search Algorithms with Python','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/search-algorithms','Learn the concepts behind linear and binary search before implementing them in Python. Test your knowledge with two quizzes. Learn to modify a version of binary search to look for data in a sparse dataset.','Codecademy','Python, Linear Search, Binary Search',4.6,9794,4500000,'04:00:00',14400,0,0,'Intermediate','Computer Science','English'),('COURSE_029','Build Chatbots with Python','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/paths/build-chatbots-with-python','Introduction to Python and Chatbots. Whet your appetite for building chatbots as you dig into Python basics. Python Data Structures and Loops. Learn Python data structures and loops, fundamentals that will help you build better chatbots and other programs. Rule-Based Chatbots. Explore natural language processing (NLP) methods and begin applying common chatbot architecture to create rule-based chatbots. Retrieval-Based Chatbots. Create retrieval-based chatbots using NLP language modeling and word embedding methods. Deep Learning and Generative Chatbots. Dig into deep learning for NLP and build an open-domain chatbot. Capstone. Put your Python and chatbot-building skills to the test in this off-platform project. Choose between retrieval-based or generative models.','Codecademy','Chatbot, Python, NLP, Deep Learning, Machine Learning, Data Structures',4.6,9794,1625989,'08:00:00',28800,0,0,'Beginner','Data Science','English'),('COURSE_030','Get started with Machine Learning','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/paths/machine-learning','Introduction to Machine Learning. Learn some of the fundamental concepts behind machine learning. Supervised Learning: Regression. Use linear regression or multiple linear regression to fit a line to data. Using this line, you can make predictions about future data. Regression Cumulative Project. Practice your regression skills on a real-world dataset provided by Yelp. Supervised Learning: Introduction to Classification. Learn to classify data using some of the most famous supervised machine learning models. Supervised Learning: Advanced Classification. Learn some of the more complicated supervised machine learning models. Supervised Machine Learning Cumulative Project. In this cumulative project, use your understanding of a variety of supervised machine learning models to analyze social media data. Unsupervised Learning. Learn how unsupervised machine learning models work by implementing the K-Means clustering algorithm. Unsupervised Machine Learning Cumulative Project. Create a project on your own computer that demonstrates your understanding of unsupervised machine learning. Perceptrons and Neural Nets. Learn the concepts behind neural nets and begin to create your own by implementing a perceptron &mdash; the building blocks of neural nets. Machine Learning Capstone Project. Use a dataset from OkCupid and the machine learning skills you have learned.','Codecademy','Python, Scikit-learn, Matplotlib, Pandas, Jupyter, Machine Learning, Deep Learning',4.6,9794,1625989,'07:00:00',25200,0,0,'Intermediate','Data Science','English'),('COURSE_031','Learn the Basics of Machine Learning','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/machine-learning','Introduction to Machine Learning. What is Machine Learning and how do we use it? Linear Regression. Given a set of points, find a line that fits the data best! Even this simple form of regression allows us to predict future points. Multiple Linear Regression uses two or more independent variables to predict the value of the dependent variable. Yelp Regression Project. Practice your regression skills on a real-world dataset provided by Yelp! Classification Vs Regression. Learn about the two types of Supervised Learning algorithms, for predicting different kinds of output. Classification: K-Nearest Neighbors. K-Nearest Neighbors is a supervised machine learning algorithm for classification. You will implement and test this algorithm on several datasets. Logistic Regression. Find the probability of data samples belonging to a specific class with one of the most popular classification algorithms. Decision Trees. In this course, you will learn how to build and use decision trees and random forests - two powerful supervised machine learning models. Clustering: K-Means. Clustering is the most well-known unsupervised learning technique. It finds structure in unlabeled data by identifying similar groups. Perception. Learn about the most basic type of neural net, the single neuron perceptron! You will use it to divide linearly-separable data.Artificial Intelligence Decision Making: Minimax. In this course, you\'ll learn how to create a game playing AI that can play Tic Tac Toe and Connect Four.','Codecademy','Machine Learning, Linear Regression, Multiple Linear Regression, Decision Tree, Logistic Regression, Deep Learning',4.6,9794,75219,'20:00:00',72000,0,0,'Intermediate','Data Science','English'),('COURSE_032','Back-End Engineer1','https://www.codecademy.com/learn/paths/back-end-engineer-career-path','Setting Up Your Dev Environment. Learn about the field of web development and the tools developers use to create websites. JavaScript Syntax, Part I. Get introduced to JavaScript and get comfortable with the basics of writing JavaScript programs. JavaScript Syntax, Part II. Discover more JavaScript techniques and features including arrays, looping, and objects. Git and Github, Part I. Learn how to use the Git version control system to keep track of changes and document your work. Then learn markdown and publish your first. JavaScript Syntax Portfolio Project. Build a Node.js console app that generates random messages each time a user runs the program and version your project with Git/GitHub. Basics of Back-End Development. Start learning about back-end development and programming servers. JavaScript Syntax, Part III. Understand intermediate JavaScript concepts, such as classes, modules, and error handling. Fundamentals of Operating Systems. Learn about how Operating Systems work. Build a Back-End with Node/Express.js. Learn about the popular back-end environment, Node.js and how to create back-end servers and APIs in JavaScript using the popular Express.js. Test Driven Development with JavaScript. Understand the fundamentals of Test Driven Development (TDD) and how you can apply its principles when developing back-ends. Website Development Fundamentals. Be introduced to the field of front-end web development and create your first web page on 